The Labour Party is no longer a diverse stream of opinion.
They are intolerant of those who express their opinions.
When Momento activists in my local party voted for my admonition, it was no surprise.
After all, I am the last in a row of Labour MPs to be told that they are not welcome - because they have honestly given their opinion.
My parliamentary colleague Joan Ryan was treated similarly because she resolutely opposed anti-Semitism.
In my case, I was criticized for disagreeing with Jeremy Corbyn.
On the importance of responsible economic policy, on national security, on Europe, paradoxically similar matters on which Jeremy disagreed with previous leaders.
The announcement of the Labour Party meeting in Nottingham East on Friday said that "we want the meetings to be accessible and productive."
For most of the eight years I was a local Labour MP, the GC meetings on Friday night were exactly like that.
