English and Bough begin their odyssey full of farcical banter: disguised as waiters, they set fire to a French restaurant; create chaos when they sneak aboard Volt's luxury yacht; and English unleashes pure anarchy when they try to get to know the interior of Volt's house using virtual reality.
All the aces are certainly ready for this last sequence, but no matter how kind and stormy it is, it has something from the children's TV in it.
Quite a moderate affair.
